  "title": "Senior QS / Quantity Surveyor Main Contractor 5 days' work week",
  "description": "<p>Assist in preparation and submission of tender quotations and ensure timeline are met for every tender.</p>\n<p>Quantity take-off for all the tenders, in the form of manual measurement and update the amendment changes of the tender</p>\n<p>During tender stages, sourcing of quotation for rates and technical data are required due to every project’s requirement varies.</p>\n<p>Arrange and carry out tender interview, negotiate of price with suppliers and subcontractors including of preparation of sub-contract agreement / letter of award.</p>\n<p>Monitoring progress claims and payments, sub-contractors payment, certification, VO submission and final accounts</p>\n<p>Assist in the settlement of final accounts with client, suppliers and subcontractors</p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<p>Minimum Diploma in Civil Engineering / Building / Quantity Surveying or equivalent</p>\n<p>Minimum 3 years of relevant work experience in construction industry</p>\n<p>Proficient in MS Office and other Measurement Software</p>",
